ðŸ’¡ Q.4 Whats difference between Inline, Inline Block and block ?
1.Inline:
Inline elements are displayed in a line, one after the other, and they do not start on a new.

2.Inline-Block:
Inline-block elements are displayed in a line, one after the other, like inline elements, but they can have a width and height set.

3.Block:
Block elements start on a new line and take up the full width available by default.
They create line breaks before and after themselves and form a block-level box.


