ðŸ’¡ Q.5 How is Border-box different from Content Box?

1.Content-Box:
Width and height are calculated based on the content size, excluding padding and border.
2.Border-Box:
Width and height include both the content size and any padding and border specified.



ðŸ’¡ Q.6 Whatâ€™s z-index and How does it Function ?

It is a CSS property that controls the stacking order of positioned elements on the z-axis. 
It determines the order in which elements are displayed on top of each other when they overlap in the document layout. 
The higher the z-index value, the closer an element is to the viewer, and it will appear on top of elements with lower z-index values.



